public class SDTaxonomyPartitionDialog
extends javax.swing.JDialog

Seed Data Taxonomy Partition selection dialog. This is the generic dialog to show Taxonomy partition values available from the current driver VO in a shuttle pick list, and allows users to select which partition values to create. Each partition value equates to a single unique Extract file, each with unique data. The values shown are either the high level Application values, or child LBAs. The SDTaxonomyDlgHelper instance passed to constructor drives which values are shown.
